EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to Medicaid; creating and prescribing the duties
of the Beneficiary Advisory Council of the Division of
Health Care Financing and Policy of the Department of
Health and Human Services; prescribing requirements
governing the membership and procedures of the Council;
revising the name of the Medical Care Advisory
Committee of the Division to the Medicaid Advisory
Committee; adding certain members to the Committee;
revising certain requirements governing the operations of
the Committee; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing federal regulations require the State to establish a Medicaid Advisory
2 Committee and a Beneficiary Advisory Council to advise the Director of the
3 Department of Health and Human Services concerning policy developments related
4 to and the effective administration of Medicaid. Existing federal regulations
5 prescribe requirements governing the membership of the Committee and Council,
6 including a requirement that a certain percentage of the voting members of the
7 Medicaid Advisory Committee concurrently serve on the Beneficiary Advisory
8 Council. (42 C.F.R. § 431.12)
9 To comply with these federal requirements, section 5 of this bill creates the
10 Beneficiary Advisory Council within the Division of Health Care Financing and
11 Policy of the Department to advise the Medicaid Advisory Committee on the
12 experience of persons who are recipients of Medicaid. Section 6 of this bill
-
